At least 1,000 Taliban prisoners are expected to released this week, five official sources said earlier, paving the way for opening direct talks between the Afghan government and the Taliban insurgents. But the Taliban want the Afghan government to release 5,000 fighters. (Reporting by Hamid Shalizi in Istanbul; Writing by Rupam Jain; Editing by Sandra Maler) Please note you must be a Maverick Insider to comment. Sign up here or sign in if you are already an Insider.